line_1: Made up in pomp the Glorious Parliament.
line_2: All met in Council for some grand Intent,
Plyes closely at the Dancing tent,
With peace or war be well content,
The members to the Mitchelgemot went,

line_1: Sate thrice, but spoke not once, in parliament;
line_2: Two good estates sir Harry Clodpole spent;

line_1: As that two Nations has one Parliament.
line_2: And that which also gives our Hearts Content,
